Boil a half-full kettle.

Pour the boiled water into a #large saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic #press{}). Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the prawns and stir-fry, ~{2-3%mins}.

Stir in the garlic, @curry powder mix{1%sachet} and @korma curry paste{50%g} to the pan and fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton} in a sieve.

Stir the chickpeas, @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and the @water{100%ml}(for the curry) into the pan.

> See pantry for amount of water for the curry.

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

When the curry has thickened, stir in the @mango chutney{40%g} and @peas{120%g}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the rice between your serving bowls.

Spoon over the prawn korma.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} to finish.

Enjoy!